}}
| ShortSummary        = Gordon unburdens himself of a few confidences and Sophie and Katey discover gold.
| LineColor           = 000000
}}
| ShortSummary        = Kuipers finds a skeleton or two and young love blossoms with Amy. Neil is treated badly and who is the woolly creature from the past?
| LineColor           = 000000
}}
| ShortSummary        = Amy and Kieran's plans are delayed when a quiet day on the river raises more than they bargained for and Gordon is caught in a web of intrigue.
| LineColor           = 000000
}}
| ShortSummary        = The talks between the Connor and Johnstone families cause problems for all; Bob's leadership qualities go bush; Val stirs up more trouble than she can handle; and Louise is plagued by rumours.
| LineColor           = 000000
}}
| ShortSummary        = Sophie thinks she has been abandoned again and a surprise tenant takes over Louise's cottage - with even more surprises at the housewarming party. Janine has had enough but support comes from an unexpected quarter.
| LineColor           = 000000
}}
| ShortSummary        = Love is in the air and everyone seems susceptible - but which couples have a future together? The only person who seems to have any stability seems to be young Sophie.
| LineColor           = 000000
}}
| ShortSummary        = Everyone's home lives seem to be in upheaval, apart from Amy and Kieran. Val's particular disaster has far-reaching consequences.
| LineColor           = 000000
}}
